desc: A Diesel-powered dory vessel of a type still in use. Built in 1914. The dories are nested on the stern, there is a gurdy amidships, and a steel anchor cable and winch forward.
source: History of the Pacific Halibut Fishery by William F. Thomson and Norman L. Freeman (1930)

desc: The "Marmot," built in 1926. A modern Diesel-powered long-line boat. Her dories are not for fishing. Note the electric lights, power gurdy, canvas shelter for bait tables, and chute on the stern. The sail is almost lacking.
source: History of the Pacific Halibut Fishery by William F. Thomson and Norman L. Freeman (1930)
